{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Protect those already on 10 year FLR FP routes from new rules changes.",
        "additional_details": "The government's proposed immigration rule changes must include grandfathering protections for families\u2014specifically,the partners and parents of British citizens\u2014who are already on the 10-year route to settlement. Applying new rules retrospectively to these families undermines their fundamental right to family life, breaches the legitimate expectation they were given, and causes severe disruption to British citizen children and their family units.",
        "background": "We are requesting the goverment to provide transitional arrangments (grandfathering protections) for those already on a 10 year route to settlement either as a partner or parent of a British citizen.",
